## Naming Conventions

- Component files в†’ `PascalCase.jsx` (e.g. `SectionHeader.jsx`)
- Data files в†’ `camelCase.js`, use `.jsx` only if the file contains JSX (inline SVG)
- Hook files в†’ `camelCase.js` prefixed with `use` (e.g. `useScrollPosition.js`)
- Utility files в†’ `camelCase.js` (e.g. `formatDate.js`)
- Every page folder в†’ must have `index.js` that re-exports the page default

## Page Section Rule

- Every page folder should split section-level UI into a local `components/` folder.
- Keep the page file focused on composition, data plumbing, and layout only.
- If a page has multiple substantial sections, each section should live in its own component file under `src/pages/[PageName]/components/`.
- Do not keep reusable or section-sized JSX inline in the page file when it can be extracted cleanly.
